# A [[Germanic]] [[language]]; the primary [[language]] of the descendants of [[Dutch]] and other European settlers, as well as many mixed-race (e.g. Rehoboth Baster) living in [[South Africa]] and in [[Namibia]]. Also, one of the eleven official languages of South Africa and until 1990 one of three official languages of Namibia.
# A [[people]] from South Africa and [[Namibia]] (who speak Afrikaans).

